Package cas2xb3_finalprototype

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AirlineVertex
    This is the airline vertex that defines specific airlines that are associated with different airports regarding lost luggage cases inside of the TSA dataset.
    AirportEdge
    The purpose of this class is to create edges between two different airports that are differentiated by ID.
    AirportGraph
    The purpose of this class is to create a standard graph from airport edges that consist of AirportVertex objects with their own IDs.
    AirportVertex
    The purpose of this class is to create an airport vertex that pertains to a name and unique ID that is given by RateMyRouteFinal.java, as well as airport code to determine whether a weight exists for one inside the connectingairpoort.txt file.
    ClaimMyBag
    This class connects the two GUIs of RateMyRoute and NewSearch by providing two buttons that will take the user to either one of the user interfaces.
    DijkstraSP
    This is the Dijkstra's algorithm that determines the shortest path from one location to another depending on a source vertex and an airport graph that is provided.
    Edge
    The purpose of this class is to create an Edge between an airport and an airline, which can be passed into the LuggageGraph to determine the ratios of lost luggage/associated airline at an airport.
    FileReading
    The purpose of this class is to be able to read from a text file that is directly correlating with a dataset that was retrieved as an Excel file.
    JUnitTesting  
    LuggageGraph
    The purpose of this class is to create a luggage graph that connects airports with airlines in the form of a multidimensional array.
    LuggageT
    The purpose of this module is to create LuggageT objects that are defined by parameters that pertain to the claims data set provided by the U.S.
    Merge
    This sorts all of the luggages by claim numbers through ArrayLists.
    NewSearch
    The purpose of this class is to provide the GUI for the NewSearch which searches for claim number inside of the luggage TSA dataset that determines locational information for lost luggage.
    RateMyRoute
    The purpose of this is to provide the GUI for the RateMyRoute portion of the project that is connected by ClaimMyBag.java to provide multiple choices of GUI for use by the user.
    RateMyRouteFinal
    This class is used to create a series of graphs in order to find a lowest risk path from one location to another that is provided by the user in terms of two airport codes and a month.
    Search
    This is used to create a Search object that can be performed binary search on when it is sorted using the Merge class.
